phrases: What is it going to take to crack the Top 50, anyway?
Well, not that I really studied that hard...
I am next to Young Mistress!
Well, I guess it is the same as usual for me.
Well, I guess I did so-so myself.
We are side by side, huh, Ruri?
He is always like that, you know.
Come to think of it, I have not spotted Tachibana's name yet.
Oh, now that you mention it...
Knowing her, I bet she is right near the top.
Wait, what is up with that?!
I am embarrassed to say it,
but studying has never been my strong suit.
You seem like the type who would have no trouble with that kind of thing.
To be honest, I have zero motivation.
You really are being honest there!
For a long time, in order to become your bride, Master Raku...
all my efforts have gone into various lessons,
and how to become as attractive a woman as possible!
I wish you would not just blurt out stuff that makes us all freeze!
Yeah, but you cannot just keep hanging on with grades like these, can you?
You could end up getting held back.
The teacher said if I got below 40 points on my next math test, I would have to re-take it.
If you do not mind, could you tutor me at my home after school?
Hey, what are you talking about?
I will thank you not to underestimate my ineptitude!
I cannot possibly improve my grades without someone is guidance!
In that case, why do not I tutor you myself?
I am sure it is more fitting for someone ranked No. 5 like me!
You do not seem like you know the first thing about teaching others, Kirisaki!
You do not mind, do you?
Since my father will not be coming home tonight,
we should be able to study to our heart's content till daybreak!
Hey, hey, let us not get ahead of ourselves, okay?
Look, I do not mind helping you out with your schoolwork...
But spending the night is going overboard, do not you think?
Since the math test is tomorrow...
Why is Kirisaki tagging along, too?
All you are doing is having friends over to study for a test,
so what is wrong with me being around, I wonder?
There is nothing wrong with it, really.
But if I may be blunt... you are like a third wheel, should I say?
You do not have to be blunt about that kind of thing!
Well, I am glad you are here.
Come on, get ready to study, will you?
We will help you with whatever you do not understand.
It is not as if you are going to be the one to teach me.
All right, I will start then.
I do not understand this problem!
You do not have to glom onto him to learn, do you?
But I would learn faster if I was next to him...
Man, thank goodness she is here, too.
Which part do not you get?
For this, you go like this...
I think I understand it just a little bit better now.
In other words, if this a is me,
the b is you, Master Raku, and the x is Kirisaki...
Then all I have to do is lock out just the x, like this!
That pisses me off, so do not memorize it that way!
Would you mind showing me how to do this, next?
I want to know how this lady feels, waiting for her husband's return in this chapter...
See, she is not just waiting.
She is about to go off and see him herself, so...
All right, on to the next problem!
What is the correct answer you should give
to a courageous girl who is cared for her beloved for ten years?
How do you solve this problem again?
If the tutor himself does not get it, how helpful is that?
You cannot just use a formula like you normally would...
My, my, did you say interfere?
By that do you mean to interfere your studying?
Or a world where only you two exist?
If the latter, I have every intention of hindering you as much as I can.
Look, you... are you at all motivated to study?
If you do not shape up, you really will repeat a grade!
Well, it is not that I am not motivated.
I simply cannot do what I cannot do.
Well, then, how did you get into our high school?
Do not tell me you got in through the backdoor?
Well, I am only joking about that,
but the day before the entrance exam, I pulled an all-nighter.
And thanks to that, I barely passed.
Hey, would not you say that in your case,
it is not a matter of you not being a good student...
I mean, it seems to me that you would start getting good grades if you really hit the books.
Give it all you have got!
I will do what I can to help you.
You do not want to get held back, do you?
In other words, you will miss me if you cannot get promoted with me, right?
I am going to do my best!
Well, you are not wrong about that, but you sure took it in a positive way!
But for some reason, having you tutor me like this reminds me of those days 10 years ago.
Wait, so you helped her with her schoolwork?
No... after all, I was only in kindergarten.
Master Raku taught me so many things.
Games that I could enjoy even if I was alone.
What was going on at kindergarten...
he would teach me the songs and talk about his friends.
They are both asleep, for crying out loud!
Well, but I cannot really blame them.
I mean, it is the dead of night...
Seriously, I do not know what it is that she sees in me.
She is a pretty weird girl, but she is a good kid.
She is hot and popular with the guys.
I am sure she could have anyone she wanted.
Being told I love you by someone...
Oh, but as long as you are okay with it, Rakkun...
Look, you - I know you are totally awake.
If you have time to mess around like that, just go to sleep!
I will work hard, all right?
Master Raku is very sweet, after all.
I suppose pulling an all-nighter can only take me so far.
But this is the problem that I did with Master Raku.
If I add up the answers that I am sure I got right, it comes out to 40 exactly!
Now I will not have to re-take the exam.
You came so close, huh, Tachibana?
It is too bad, but you are going to have to re-take the test, huh?
Well, but considering you got a zero on your last math test, I would say you did real good.
Looks like she re-wrote this answer here.
And she got it right the first time.
Unfortunately, it looks like I will have to re-take the exam,
so please tutor me again, will you?
At least try to study on your own a little!
Well, you are asking for the impossible.
Studying all night... you are pushing yourself too hard.
If it takes too great a toll on you...
It is nothing I cannot handle.
It happened during that Culture Festival as well.
You have been pushing yourself too hard lately.
You do not have to tell me.
I am by your side to watch over you.
You do not have to tell me.
So you want me to take care of him?
I will be away on a trip with my father for just one day.
I like taking care of animals anyway.
I will have to thank you in some way, sometime.
Hey, does this little guy talk or something?
He is very smart, you know.
To Master Raku A love note
I have summarized how to take care of him,
and what to watch out for in this note.
I am really counting on you!
Why would she pick out a name like that, of all things?
I do not know if she is needling me or if she is serious.
Crap, you look like a dimwit!
Come to think of it, we do not have parrots at school
so this will be my first time looking after one.
Since you are a parrot, I would love to see you talk.
Are you about to say something?
What does she think she is doing?!
Seriously, what the hell does she think she is doing?!
It is almost time to feed you.
You are hungry, are not you?
Raku absolutely will not eat unless you say,
'Here, Master Raku... ahhh!' with all your sincerity.
That girl... what kind of training is that?!
How did I ever end up like this?
But hey, never mind the content...
this little guy can speak pretty fluently.
Wonder if he will learn to say what I teach him?
Master Raku, you are so cool!
Master Raku, you are so cool!
Wait, did you get what I just said?
Okay, I am going to make you learn no matter what!
try saying How much wood would a woodchuck chuck, if a woodchuck could chuck wood?
I am talking to you, Master Raku!
Young Master... what is up with that, I wonder?
How much wood would a woodchuck chuck, if a woodchuck could chuck wood?
Naming his pet after himself, even sticking on a Master.
Well, I am sure Young Master has his reasons.
I got so caught up in teaching him phrases.
And he never did learn to say any of them.
A pet that I was entrusted with!
Thank goodness you did not get too far!
You must not touch me there!
Oh, what is the problem, Marika?
Your body does not seem to be resisting me.
Master Raku, you are so mean!
I have got to do something about this right away!
It is not even a matter of Tachibana never forgiving me...
My reputation around the neighborhood will be in shreds!
You know you can always come to us with any problem.
Young Master's in the throes of adolescence!
But really, your face pisses me off for some reason, you know?
You kind of remind of that moron...
You must not be so rough with me!
Not that I do not find that attractive, too.
By any chance did a parrot come flying by?
I am taking care of him for Tachibana, see.
Did you see which way he...
Make amends by dying, you dumbass!
What is your problem, for Pete's sake?
Dammit, I never have any clue what she is thinking.
I swear I am going to catch him this time.
I wonder where he came from?
Did he escape from somewhere, I wonder?
You really have a way with any kind of animal, huh, Sis?
Do you know where your owner is?
Really, I do not believe you, Master Raku!
Oh, no, was I too late?
It is not what you think!
Just hear me out and you will see!
I have not heard anything, and I have not seen anything, so it is all good, okay?
You are the only one that I love!
Come back here, you dumbass bird!
Or I will end up frying you and eating you up, dammit!
I want to set the record straight,
but if I do not go after him, it will mean more grief for me!
I got to catch him as soon as possible!
See, there is this pet parrot...
You have been with Marika Tachibana...
Dammit, I am never going to get anywhere like this.
Does it say anything in that note?
If Master Raku escapes, this is the retrieval process
What the hell is she going to make me yell all over town?!
You come back here, Raku Ichijo!
But unless I catch that bird, I cannot make things right.
Say this in a loud voice?
What are you doing in a place like this?
It is so good to see you looking well!
Were you a good parrot while I was away?
Do you know what that parrot's been saying?
Oh, you should not take any of that at face value.
All right, if you will excuse me now.
Master Raku, I will thank you another time.
For some reason, she left without making a fuss today, do not you think?
The operation was a resounding success!
Now, then, Master Raku, I want you to learn this phrase next.
And try to really nail it!
